= Rules of Procedure =

Rules of Procedure are formal descriptions about the way an institution works. It is very helpful to know that when you deal with state organisations.

= EU institutions =


== General ==
   * [http://europa.eu.int/eur-lex/en/treaties/dat/treaties_en.pdf EU Treaties, big pdf], [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaties_of_the_European_Union Wikipedia: EU Treaties]
   * [http://europa.eu.int/eur-lex/en/treaties/selected/livre305.html Protocol on the role of national parliaments in the European Union]
   * [http://kwiki.ffii.org/index.cgi?CodecisionPosterEn FFII Codecision flowchart]
   * [http://europa.eu.int/abouteuropa/index_en.htm EUROPA] [http://europa.eu.int/comm/codecision/stepbystep/diagram_en.htm Codecision flowchart]

== European Parliament (EP) ==

   * [http://www2.europarl.eu.int/omk/sipade2?PROG=RULES-EP&L=EN&REF=TOC Rules of Procedure of the European Parliament]
     * [http://www2.europarl.eu.int/omk/sipade2?PUBREF=-//EP//TEXT+RULES-EP+20040720+RULE-061+DOC+XML+V0//EN&HNAV=Y Rule 61: Rejection of the Common Position] - according to Rule 61(2), ''"Parliament may, on the recommendation of the rapporteur, consider a further proposal for rejection after voting on the amendments and hearing a statement from the Commission pursuant to Rule 62(5)."''

   * FFII wiki: [:EuroparlSwpat04En: page about a renewed referral to the EP]

